{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":470,"text":"As an architect, I often ask myself,"},{"time":2919,"text":"what is the origin of the forms that we design?"},{"time":5759,"text":"What kind of forms could we design"},{"time":8664,"text":"if we wouldn't work with references anymore?"},{"time":11487,"text":"If we had no bias, if we had no preconceptions,"},{"time":14872,"text":"what kind of forms could we design"},{"time":17079,"text":"if we could free ourselves from"},{"time":18679,"text":"our experience?"},{"time":20815,"text":"If we could free ourselves from our education?"},{"time":25549,"text":"What would these unseen forms look like?"},{"time":28576,"text":"Would they surprise us? Would they intrigue us?"},{"time":32287,"text":"Would they delight us?"},{"time":34702,"text":"If so, then how can we go about creating something that is truly new?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":38623,"text":"I propose we look to nature."},{"time":41015,"text":"Nature has been called the greatest architect of forms."},{"time":45279,"text":"And I'm not saying that we should copy nature,"},{"time":48867,"text":"I'm not saying we should mimic biology,"},{"time":51247,"text":"instead I propose that we can borrow nature's processes."},{"time":54695,"text":"We can abstract them and to create something that is new."},{"time":59149,"text":"Nature's main process of creation, morphogenesis,"},{"time":63027,"text":"is the splitting of one cell into two cells."},{"time":66856,"text":"And these cells can either be identical,"},{"time":68913,"text":"or they can be distinct from each other"},{"time":71088,"text":"through asymmetric cell division."}]},{"cues":[{"time":73152,"text":"If we abstract this process, and simplify it as much as possible,"},{"time":76951,"text":"then we could start with a single sheet of paper,"},{"time":79184,"text":"one surface, and we could make a fold"},{"time":81680,"text":"and divide the surface into two surfaces."},{"time":84616,"text":"We're free to choose where we make the fold."},{"time":86879,"text":"And by doing so, we can differentiate the surfaces."},{"time":91789,"text":"Through this very simple process,"},{"time":93683,"text":"we can create an astounding variety of forms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":97295,"text":"Now, we can take this form and use the same process"},{"time":100020,"text":"to generate three-dimensional structures,"},{"time":102012,"text":"but rather than folding things by hand,"},{"time":104420,"text":"we'll bring the structure into the computer,"},{"time":107005,"text":"and code it as an algorithm."},{"time":109980,"text":"And in doing so, we can suddenly fold anything."},{"time":112988,"text":"We can fold a million times faster,"},{"time":115147,"text":"we can fold in hundreds and hundreds of variations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118308,"text":"And as we're seeking to make something three-dimensional,"},{"time":120788,"text":"we start not with a single surface, but with a volume."},{"time":124004,"text":"A simple volume, the cube."},{"time":125357,"text":"If we take its surfaces and fold them"},{"time":127077,"text":"again and again and again and again,"},{"time":129133,"text":"then after 16 iterations, 16 steps,"},{"time":131996,"text":"we end up with 400,000 surfaces and a shape that looks,"},{"time":135845,"text":"for instance, like this."},{"time":138380,"text":"And if we change where we make the folds,"},{"time":141092,"text":"if we change the folding ratio,"},{"time":142733,"text":"then this cube turns into this one."},{"time":146156,"text":"We can change the folding ratio again to produce this shape,"},{"time":150295,"text":"or this shape."}]},{"cues":[{"time":152122,"text":"So we exert control over the form"},{"time":153745,"text":"by specifying the position of where we're making the fold,"},{"time":157249,"text":"but essentially you're looking at a folded cube."},{"time":161955,"text":"And we can play with this."},{"time":163019,"text":"We can apply different folding ratios to different parts"},{"time":165635,"text":"of the form to create local conditions."},{"time":168380,"text":"We can begin to sculpt the form."}]},{"cues":[{"time":170323,"text":"And because we're doing the folding on the computer,"},{"time":173211,"text":"we are completely free of any physical constraints."},{"time":176907,"text":"So that means that surfaces can intersect themselves,"},{"time":179858,"text":"they can become impossibly small."},{"time":181347,"text":"We can make folds that we otherwise could not make."},{"time":184948,"text":"Surfaces can become porous."},{"time":186826,"text":"They can stretch. They can tear."},{"time":189555,"text":"And all of this expounds the scope of forms that we can produce."}]},{"cues":[{"time":194190,"text":"But in each case, I didn't design the form."},{"time":196940,"text":"I designed the process that generated the form."},{"time":201541,"text":"In general, if we make a small change to the folding ratio,"},{"time":206029,"text":"which is what you're seeing here,"},{"time":207624,"text":"then the form changes correspondingly."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211397,"text":"But that's only half of the story --"},{"time":213653,"text":"99.9 percent of the folding ratios produce not this,"},{"time":217976,"text":"but this, the geometric equivalent of noise."},{"time":222872,"text":"The forms that I showed before were made actually"},{"time":224992,"text":"through very long trial and error."},{"time":226640,"text":"A far more effective way to create forms, I have found,"},{"time":229856,"text":"is to use information that is already contained in forms."},{"time":233744,"text":"A very simple form such as this one actually contains"},{"time":236399,"text":"a lot of information that may not be visible to the human eye."},{"time":239991,"text":"So, for instance, we can plot the length of the edges."},{"time":242472,"text":"White surfaces have long edges, black ones have short ones."},{"time":245808,"text":"We can plot the planarity of the surfaces, their curvature,"},{"time":249385,"text":"how radial they are -- all information that may not be"},{"time":253472,"text":"instantly visible to you,"},{"time":255419,"text":"but that we can bring out, that we can articulate,"},{"time":257844,"text":"and that we can use to control the folding."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261220,"text":"So now I'm not specifying a single"},{"time":263179,"text":"ratio anymore to fold it,"},{"time":265355,"text":"but instead I'm establishing a rule,"},{"time":267907,"text":"I'm establishing a link between a property of a surface"},{"time":270343,"text":"and how that surface is folded."},{"time":273316,"text":"And because I've designed the process and not the form,"},{"time":276267,"text":"I can run the process again and again and again"},{"time":278589,"text":"to produce a whole family of forms."}]},{"cues":[{"time":293385,"text":"These forms look elaborate, but the process is a very minimal one."},{"time":297828,"text":"There is a simple input,"},{"time":298957,"text":"it's always a cube that I start with,"},{"time":300909,"text":"and it's a very simple operation -- it's making a fold,"},{"time":304485,"text":"and doing this over and over again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308437,"text":"So let's bring this process to architecture."},{"time":310717,"text":"How? And at what scale?"},{"time":312317,"text":"I chose to design a column."},{"time":314045,"text":"Columns are architectural archetypes."},{"time":317421,"text":"They've been used throughout history to express ideals"},{"time":320488,"text":"about beauty, about technology."},{"time":325563,"text":"A challenge to me was how we could express"},{"time":327485,"text":"this new algorithmic order in a column."},{"time":330781,"text":"I started using four cylinders."},{"time":333765,"text":"Through a lot of experimentation, these cylinders"},{"time":337541,"text":"eventually evolved into this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":340676,"text":"And these columns, they have information at very many scales."},{"time":345292,"text":"We can begin to zoom into them."},{"time":347810,"text":"The closer one gets, the more new features one discovers."},{"time":351365,"text":"Some formations are almost at the threshold of human visibility."},{"time":355037,"text":"And unlike traditional architecture,"},{"time":356989,"text":"it's a single process that creates both the overall form"},{"time":359773,"text":"and the microscopic surface detail."},{"time":365118,"text":"These forms are undrawable."},{"time":367809,"text":"An architect who's drawing them with a pen and a paper"},{"time":371185,"text":"would probably take months,"},{"time":372977,"text":"or it would take even a year to draw all the sections,"},{"time":375361,"text":"all of the elevations, you can only create something like this"},{"time":377665,"text":"through an algorithm."}]},{"cues":[{"time":379801,"text":"The more interesting question, perhaps, is,"},{"time":381833,"text":"are these forms imaginable?"},{"time":384462,"text":"Usually, an architect can somehow envision the end state"},{"time":387097,"text":"of what he is designing."},{"time":388961,"text":"In this case, the process is deterministic."},{"time":391786,"text":"There's no randomness involved at all,"},{"time":394145,"text":"but it's not entirely predictable."},{"time":396152,"text":"There's too many surfaces,"},{"time":397728,"text":"there's too much detail, one can't see the end state."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401338,"text":"So this leads to a new role for the architect."},{"time":404552,"text":"One needs a new method to explore all of the possibilities"},{"time":408163,"text":"that are out there."},{"time":409939,"text":"For one thing, one can design many variants of a form,"},{"time":413171,"text":"in parallel, and one can cultivate them."},{"time":415385,"text":"And to go back to the analogy with nature,"},{"time":417633,"text":"one can begin to think in terms of populations,"},{"time":420129,"text":"one can talk about permutations, about generations,"},{"time":423657,"text":"about crossing and breeding to come up with a design."},{"time":428520,"text":"And the architect is really, he moves into the position"},{"time":430905,"text":"of being an orchestrator of all of these processes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":434337,"text":"But enough of the theory."},{"time":436681,"text":"At one point I simply wanted to jump inside"},{"time":439208,"text":"this image, so to say, I bought these red and blue"},{"time":443037,"text":"3D glasses, got up very close to the screen,"},{"time":445973,"text":"but still that wasn't the same as being able to"},{"time":448045,"text":"walk around and touch things."},{"time":450397,"text":"So there was only one possibility --"},{"time":452300,"text":"to bring the column out of the computer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":455397,"text":"There's been a lot of talk now about 3D printing."},{"time":458317,"text":"For me, or for my purpose at this moment,"},{"time":461276,"text":"there's still too much of an unfavorable tradeoff"},{"time":464358,"text":"between scale, on the one hand, and resolution and speed, on the other."},{"time":471141,"text":"So instead, we decided to take the column,"},{"time":473398,"text":"and we decided to build it as a layered model,"},{"time":475837,"text":"made out of very many slices, thinly stacked over each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":479965,"text":"What you're looking at here is an X-ray"},{"time":481862,"text":"of the column that you just saw, viewed from the top."},{"time":484637,"text":"Unbeknownst to me at the time,"},{"time":486637,"text":"because we had only seen the outside,"},{"time":489013,"text":"the surfaces were continuing to fold themselves,"},{"time":491173,"text":"to grow on the inside of the column,"},{"time":493437,"text":"which was quite a surprising discovery."},{"time":495983,"text":"From this shape, we calculated a cutting line,"},{"time":499597,"text":"and then we gave this cutting line to a laser cutter"},{"time":502621,"text":"to produce -- and you're seeing a segment of it here --"},{"time":506435,"text":"very many thin slices, individually cut, on top of each other."}]},{"cues":[{"time":513480,"text":"And this is a photo now, it's not a rendering,"},{"time":516293,"text":"and the column that we ended up with"},{"time":518093,"text":"after a lot of work, ended up looking remarkably like the one"},{"time":521140,"text":"that we had designed in the computer."},{"time":524850,"text":"Almost all of the details, almost all of the"},{"time":526971,"text":"surface intricacies were preserved."}]},{"cues":[{"time":532626,"text":"But it was very labor intensive."},{"time":534972,"text":"There's a huge disconnect at the moment still"},{"time":537373,"text":"between the virtual and the physical."},{"time":540133,"text":"It took me several months to design the column,"},{"time":542259,"text":"but ultimately it takes the computer about 30 seconds"},{"time":544977,"text":"to calculate all of the 16 million faces."},{"time":547825,"text":"The physical model, on the other hand,"},{"time":549786,"text":"is 2,700 layers, one millimeter thick,"},{"time":553994,"text":"it weighs 700 kilos, it's made of sheet that can cover"},{"time":558141,"text":"this entire auditorium."},{"time":560279,"text":"And the cutting path that the laser followed"},{"time":562367,"text":"goes from here to the airport and back again."}]},{"cues":[{"time":567484,"text":"But it is increasingly possible."},{"time":569233,"text":"Machines are getting faster, it's getting less expensive,"},{"time":571844,"text":"and there's some promising technological developments"},{"time":574604,"text":"just on the horizon."},{"time":576387,"text":"These are images from the Gwangju Biennale."},{"time":579459,"text":"And in this case, I used ABS plastic to produce the columns,"},{"time":582983,"text":"we used the bigger, faster machine,"},{"time":584837,"text":"and they have a steel core inside, so they're structural,"},{"time":587894,"text":"they can bear loads for once."},{"time":590870,"text":"Each column is effectively a hybrid of two columns."},{"time":592885,"text":"You can see a different column in the mirror,"},{"time":596294,"text":"if there's a mirror behind the column"},{"time":598344,"text":"that creates a sort of an optical illusion."}]},{"cues":[{"time":601431,"text":"So where does this leave us?"},{"time":603262,"text":"I think this project gives us a glimpse of the unseen objects that await us"},{"time":607730,"text":"if we as architects begin to think about designing not the object,"},{"time":611613,"text":"but a process to generate objects."},{"time":615006,"text":"I've shown one simple process that was inspired by nature;"},{"time":618279,"text":"there's countless other ones."},{"time":621127,"text":"In short, we have no constraints."},{"time":624574,"text":"Instead, we have processes in our hands right now"},{"time":628144,"text":"that allow us to create structures at all scales"},{"time":632725,"text":"that we couldn't even have dreamt up."},{"time":635757,"text":"And, if I may add, at one point we will build them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":640576,"text":"Thank you. (Applause)"}]}]}